1
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,180
What is this again?

2
00:01:27,700 --> 00:01:29,980
Don't you have other things to do
besides this?

3
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:32,600
Sorry sir, this lane is closed temporarily.

4
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:35,060
You can turn around through the other way.

5
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:36,500
Please understand.

6
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:38,160
Go on.

7
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,100
But I'm gonna be late!

8
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:43,100
This is a very important order package.

9
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,450
If this package is not delivered on time...

10
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:46,280
Who do you think will be responsible?!

11
00:01:46,660 --> 00:01:51,840
Geez, Okay. Just be quick, all right?

12
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,000
You can pass.

13
00:01:54,260 --> 00:01:55,240
Come on.

14
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:02,440
What a really bad day...

15
00:02:04,140 --> 00:02:06,240
Rough morning. What more...

16
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:12,900
Dammit!

17
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,100
Dammit!!

18
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:40,200
As if anything else
could go worse!

19
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:34,400
"TRAIN TO BUSAN"

20
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,160
Sunbaenim,

21
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:40,500
statistical data companies showed
abnormal stock market returns.

22
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:43,040
What we need is to take action
as soon as possible.

23
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,260
In order to secure our position in this stock market.

24
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:47,860
Yes.

25
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:49,000
Thank you for the instructions.

26
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:56,360
I will do it as soon as possible.

27
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,260
Yes.

28
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,460
It will be done as you wish.

29
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,180
Yeah yeah.

30
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:03,160
Have a nice day!

31
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,100
Come into my office.

32
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,480
Yes, director?

33
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,880
Secure all of our assets in the stock market.

34
00:04:42,460 --> 00:04:43,400
All of them?

35
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:44,400
Yes.

36
00:04:45,050 --> 00:04:47,160
Is it not too risky to do this?

37
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,350
We could still maintain our first assets...

38
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,300
and wait if something better comes...

39
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,040
Mr. Kim...

40
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:53,360
Yes sir?

41
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,400
You just do what I tell you to do.

42
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,680
We must be careful of the
possibilities that may happen.

43
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:02,480
Yes sir.

44
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:06,760
One more thing Mr Kim...

45
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,340
What's the popular gift for kids nowadays?

46
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:22,300
<i>Forget it. You really can't be a good dad to Soo-an.
You didn't even attend her recital.</i>

47
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:25,240
You know I'm busy at work.

48
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,340
She can stay here in Seoul with me.

49
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,900
<i>Just send her here in Busan!</i>

50
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:30,900
<i>You've already broke your promises!</i>

51
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:35,040
<i>How many times have you told her
you'll come come with her.</i>

52
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,900
<i>Can you keep it just this once?</i>

53
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:38,900
Yes, I promise we'll go there soon!

54
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,900
<i>I don't believe you.</i>

55
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,740
Take my word for it.

56
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,800
<i>Anyway you have to keep your promise.</i>

57
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,900
<i>Our daughter is tired
of your broken promises.</i>

58
00:05:48,180 --> 00:05:49,200
Nevermind, talk to you later.

59
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,980
<i>You know that its her birthday tomorrow right?</i>

60
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,440
I know!

61
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,720
Let me help you with that.

62
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,120
Thank you.

63
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,460
How is she?

64
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:29,740
She's playing in her room.

65
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:36,060
When are we going there?
Don't know when.

66
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:38,300
Mom doesn't talk to Dad, huh?

67
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,600
I have to go. Dad is here.

68
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,700
Soo-ann why are you awake?

69
00:06:59,940 --> 00:07:01,300
I can't sleep

70
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,660
Your mom and I talked.

71
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:11,520
I promised your mom we'd go together.

72
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,240
But before that there are things
I have to do...

73
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:17,300
Soo-an you have to be patient.

74
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,300
Open it.

75
00:07:31,780 --> 00:07:34,500
You thought I forgot?
Happy birthday.

76
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,600
Open it now.

77
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:57,660
What's wrong...
Don't you like it?

78
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,800
Could you replace this one?

79
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:21,000
Maybe we could?

80
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,900
What do you want?

81
00:08:24,660 --> 00:08:25,640
Busan.

82
00:08:26,220 --> 00:08:28,300
I want to go to mom at Busan.

83
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:29,700
Tomorrow.

84
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,760
Yeah, just wait.

85
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,160
We'll certainly go there once
your dad is done with work.

86
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:35,000
No.

87
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,360
Tomorrow.

88
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:39,100
You always make promises you can't keep.

89
00:08:39,180 --> 00:08:40,800
We have to go tomorrow
no matter what.

90
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:44,320
Are you not tired of working
all the time?

91
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,500
Grant my wish for once.

92
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,700
What did your daughter said?

93
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:58,000
She wants us to have a vacation.

94
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:02,000
Does she want to go to Busan?

95
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,520
Yes.

96
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:10,020
Since the divorce, she loves you both less.

97
00:09:11,540 --> 00:09:15,200
She misses the times when her parents
were still together.

98
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,260
As if she wants her family reunited again.

99
00:09:18,580 --> 00:09:21,900
There's nothing wrong with your family
being reunited again.

100
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:26,540
Try it this time so your family
is back together again.

101
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,380
Ma...

102
00:09:27,580 --> 00:09:28,940
I do not want to talk about it...

103
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:34,020
Let it be the past...

104
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,240
Okay.

105
00:09:38,420 --> 00:09:41,140
Don't be too busy with work...

106
00:09:43,180 --> 00:09:46,160
Sometimes you should not always focus on work.
Soo-an is growing up.

107
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,280
She also needs you.

108
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:53,680
Take care of your family, especially Soo-an.

109
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,900
<i>Come on Soo-an, cheer up!</i>

110
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,900
<i>It's okay, continue singing...</i>

111
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:44,900
<i>Please give a round of applause
to Soo-an!</i>

112
00:10:57,824 --> 00:10:58,824
<i>Okay.</i>

113
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,300
<i>Yes...ma..</i>

114
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,880
<i>Okay.</i>

115
00:11:02,940 --> 00:11:03,840
No.

116
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,420
I'm with dad.

117
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:10,600
Yeah, see you there...

118
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:30,600
Hey Soo-an, isn't your song
finished yet?

119
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:34,100
How did you know?
You weren't there.

120
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:39,600
Dad always know what you've been doing.

121
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:42,600
You got nervous right? Am I right?

122
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,260
Yes...

123
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:45,960
Okay.

124
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,880
You know you have to finish
that song.

125
00:11:51,340 --> 00:11:55,140
When you start something.
You should finish it no matter what.

126
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,700
Always remember that.

127
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:10,980
Ahh... that was close.

128
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,680
What's going on?

129
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,240
It's like raining ashes.

130
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:30,160
It looks like a big fire.

131
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,700
Hopefully there were no casualties.

132
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:07,260
<i>All departing passengers, kindly board the train now
as this train is now ready to depart for Busan.</i>

133
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:08,700
Excuse me, where is the south station?

134
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,440
Ah, South station,
you need to go that way..

135
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,360
Thank you.

136
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:41,800
Hold on, hold on...
Your scarf...

137
00:13:49,780 --> 00:13:52,940
Please rest during this trip.

138
00:13:53,020 --> 00:13:54,240
Good.

139
00:13:56,980 --> 00:13:58,900
Wow, Jin-Hee is here.

140
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,640
What do you mean,
I'm coming with you guys.

141
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,240
I'm your cheerleader.

142
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,500
How are you guys doing?

143
00:14:11,540 --> 00:14:12,660
Good.

144
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:17,480
Finally, something fresh for the eyes!

145
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,040
Finally!

146
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:23,960
Hey, it's rude to take something
that's not yours.

147
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:25,780
You really hate to share.

148
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:30,140
Hey, maybe if we were lovers
you're gonna share...

149
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,380
I might even share my bed with you...

150
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:35,460
Wow, very tempting!

151
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:42,080
Share with her! Share with her!
Share with her! Share with her!

152
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:47,260
You want some?

153
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,220
Oh my God!

154
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:53,080
Don't eat too much eggs...
You'll be passing gas later...

155
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:54,080
Here take it.

156
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,100
- Eat...
- No thanks.

157
00:14:57,640 --> 00:15:01,180
- <i>Sunbaenim, are you on the train?</i>
- Yes, we're on the train.

158
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:06,400
<i>Stop thinking about work...
We'll take care of it.</i>

159
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:07,840
Okay.

160
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:11,340
We will discuss it again after this holiday.

161
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:13,640
He manages the company well.

162
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:16,020
- See you later.
- <i>Good.</i>

163
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:28,340
- This is not happening...
- This is not happening...

164
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,520
Please don't let this happen!

165
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,300
- Choi Gyo..
- Yes.

166
00:16:43,660 --> 00:16:45,220
- Can you please check lavatory?
- Okay.

167
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:48,680
- I'd been waiting to go to the lavatory.
- It's occupied.

168
00:16:49,040 --> 00:16:51,220
Ask what's happening in there.

169
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,520
I'm afraid something happened to him.

170
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,700
Yes, he's been there a long time.

171
00:16:57,240 --> 00:17:00,360
Well, I will check ...
Please wait a moment...

172
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:11,820
Sir?

173
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,500
Sir?

174
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:20,040
Sir?

175
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:31,620
Sir?

176
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:33,880
Sir?

177
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:36,720
Do you have a ticket?

178
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:42,220
Sir, do you have a ticket?

179
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:45,500
If you don't, we need to drop
you off on the next station.

180
00:17:46,580 --> 00:17:47,840
Everyone is dead.

181
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,420
- Everyone is dead.
- What?

182
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,500
Hey little girl!

183
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:03,500
What are you doing here?

184
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:08,500
I think there are zombies hiding here.

185
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:12,500
There are no zombies in modern times like this.

186
00:18:12,820 --> 00:18:14,800
Sir, you must come with me to the back.

187
00:18:53,260 --> 00:18:54,180
Lavatory?

188
00:18:55,860 --> 00:18:58,520
We'll, you'll need to find another place
because my pregnant wife is there.

189
00:18:59,420 --> 00:19:01,820
Go through there...
go.

190
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:06,940
It will really take a while.

191
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:10,420
Baby? How are you doing in there?

192
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:14,500
Ahhh... sorry, go ahead.
Take your time... take your time.

193
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,880
Please go ahead.

194
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:17,480
Go there, go there.

195
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:22,880
She's gone, she's gone.
Relax... relax...

196
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,440
Miss?
Are you okay?

197
00:19:34,660 --> 00:19:36,480
Miss?
Oh what to do?

198
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:40,680
There's an emergency at car 11!

199
00:19:41,140 --> 00:19:41,920
Chief!

200
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,460
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Yes, Kim?

201
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:59,960
<i>It's more serious than we anticipated.</i>

202
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,200
<i>It's not just an overnight Ansan incident.</i>

203
00:20:02,620 --> 00:20:06,960
<i>I don't know whats happening,
but it's not a simple strike.</i>

204
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:09,220
MILITARY DEPLOYED TO CONTROL RIOTS
- <i>They say it's nationwide.</i>

205
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:11,860
What about breathing?
- <i>Hello?</i>

206
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:15,840
<i>But I can't seem to
control her seizure!</i>

207
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:17,780
<i>Sir, what should we do?</i>

208
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,680
I'll call you back.

209
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:33,220
INDISCRIMINATE VIOLENCE AT RIOT
<i>Oh no, they'll get hurt.</i>

210
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:34,880
That's terrible.

211
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:37,960
These people are crazy!

212
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:41,060
They should be shot and killed.

213
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,600
You mustn't say that.

214
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:45,588
Look, look.

215
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:48,480
What's up with them?

216
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:50,780
Miss?

217
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:53,960
What must I do?

218
00:20:57,660 --> 00:21:00,120
Chief? Chief where are you?

219
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,420
I don't believe this...

220
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:15,540
Chief?

221
00:21:31,220 --> 00:21:33,180
Min Jin? Min Jin?

222
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:01,600
What is that?

223
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:05,520
What is happening?!

224
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:08,600
What is this?

225
00:22:23,580 --> 00:22:26,800
Excuse me. Excuse me. Excuse me.

226
00:22:50,069 --> 00:22:52,068
Hurry! Everyone Run!

227
00:22:52,069 --> 00:22:53,069
Stand up!

228
00:22:56,180 --> 00:23:00,660
Conductor! We have a situation here!

229
00:23:13,860 --> 00:23:14,760
Run! Run!

230
00:23:35,921 --> 00:23:38,421
- Oh my god!
- What the hell?!

231
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,480
Get away! Just go!

232
00:23:57,260 --> 00:24:00,090
Get out of here! Head for the back!

233
00:24:00,190 --> 00:24:01,540
Get up! Hurry!

234
00:24:23,720 --> 00:24:24,580
Daddy!

235
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:07,820
Baby?

236
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:12,160
Sang Hwa! So damn loud!

237
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:14,210
Sorry, the thing is..

238
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:15,800
Get off me!

239
00:25:27,285 --> 00:25:28,817
You idiot! Go help her!

240
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:32,140
Hey!

241
00:25:32,220 --> 00:25:33,760
What's with you?!

242
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:38,600
Have you gone mad?!

243
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:54,600
Baby?

244
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:56,720
Sung-Gyeong!

245
00:25:59,420 --> 00:26:00,800
You can run, right?

246
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:20,580
<i>MASSIVE VIOLENCE, INCREASING CASUALTIES</i>

247
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:22,940
Get away!

248
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:35,780
Get the door! The door!

249
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:38,160
Shut the door!

250
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:40,590
Quick!

251
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:42,800
Shut it!

252
00:26:44,380 --> 00:26:45,560
Shut it now!

253
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:48,900
Just shut it!

254
00:26:56,470 --> 00:26:57,760
I know him!

255
00:27:10,760 --> 00:27:12,280
Where's the lock?

256
00:27:13,380 --> 00:27:15,260
Buddy! How do I lock this?

257
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:18,920
Do you hear me?!

258
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:23,960
Let it go.

259
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:25,920
What?

260
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:31,180
I don't think they know how to open it.

261
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:43,120
They attack because they see us.

262
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:05,650
What in the...

263
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:07,140
What are they?

264
00:28:11,460 --> 00:28:12,560
Soo-an, you okay?

265
00:28:14,535 --> 00:28:15,535
Hey buddy.

266
00:28:16,860 --> 00:28:17,720
What is it?

267
00:28:19,660 --> 00:28:21,460
Don't you owe me an apology?

268
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:22,810
What do you mean?

269
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:24,620
Look at this chump.

270
00:28:25,410 --> 00:28:28,340
You shut the door in our faces, asshole!

271
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,720
You weren't the only ones in danger!

272
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,860
What a piece of work.

273
00:28:34,940 --> 00:28:35,820
Come here.

274
00:28:35,860 --> 00:28:37,520
I'll feed you to them.

275
00:28:37,674 --> 00:28:38,674
Stop it!

276
00:28:39,060 --> 00:28:40,640
Everyone's just scared.

277
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:47,500
<i>Attention please!</i>

278
00:28:47,820 --> 00:28:52,980
<i>Due to our current situation,
we won't be stopping in Cheonan.</i>

279
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:56,800
<i>For your safety,
please stay in your seats.</i>

280
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,080
Hello? Anyone there?

281
00:29:04,750 --> 00:29:06,440
<i>Yes, go ahead.</i>

282
00:29:06,520 --> 00:29:10,280
Do you even know
what's going on back here?

283
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:12,460
Why aren't you stopping in Cheonan?

284
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,740
<i>We're aware, sir.</i>

285
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:16,840
<i>This is an order from the control center.</i>

286
00:29:17,170 --> 00:29:18,400
<i>Please be seated.</i>

287
00:29:18,580 --> 00:29:23,160
That's nonsense!
People are going rabid!

288
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,560
Stop in Cheonan, get it?!

289
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:28,280
Excuse me.

290
00:29:32,340 --> 00:29:35,240
I'm really sorry,
but could she sit down?

291
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,460
She's pregnant.

292
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:37,570
Okay.

293
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:38,830
Sit, sit.

294
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:39,560
Thank you.

295
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,860
<i>MOTHER</i>

296
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:44,420
Yes mom?

297
00:29:44,567 --> 00:29:48,067
<i>Are you on your way?</i>

298
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:50,640
Yes, we're en route.

299
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:53,700
<i>Where are you?
Why is it so loud?</i>

300
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:57,900
<i>What's happening? Everyone's fighting.</i>

301
00:29:58,260 --> 00:30:01,560
<i>Are you and Soo-an okay?</i>

302
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:04,240
Why're you breathing like that,
are you hurt?

303
00:30:05,900 --> 00:30:08,440
<i>Seok-Woo, my baby.</i>

304
00:30:09,020 --> 00:30:13,760
<i>Please take care of Soo-an.</i>

305
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:15,140
Mom, you okay?

306
00:30:16,740 --> 00:30:19,520
<i>My dear Soo-an...</i>

307
00:30:22,660 --> 00:30:28,320
<i>I love her so much,
but she only wants her mom...</i>

308
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:32,620
<i>That bitch!</i>

309
00:30:41,020 --> 00:30:41,900
Mom?

310
00:30:44,700 --> 00:30:45,440
<i>Dad.</i>

311
00:30:47,959 --> 00:30:48,959
<i>Dad!</i>

312
00:30:51,020 --> 00:30:52,880
Is granny okay?

313
00:31:01,420 --> 00:31:02,820
What the hell?

314
00:31:04,620 --> 00:31:06,140
Soo-an, sit down.

315
00:31:51,020 --> 00:31:52,640
<i>My fellow citizens,</i>

316
00:31:53,461 --> 00:31:59,961
<i>we're currently experiencing
violent riots in all major cities,</i>

317
00:32:00,438 --> 00:32:04,938
<i>resulting in many civilians and police injuries.</i>

318
00:32:05,740 --> 00:32:10,120
<i>Riots led to shutting down of various districts,</i>

319
00:32:10,390 --> 00:32:14,980
<i>and the rioters have forcibly attempted to destroy</i>

320
00:32:15,340 --> 00:32:17,840
<i>and take over government property,</i>

321
00:32:19,660 --> 00:32:23,000
<i>For this reason,
we're entering state of emergency</i>

322
00:32:23,870 --> 00:32:30,040
<i>in order to control current situations.</i>

323
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:38,580
<i>Thanks to our government's rapid response,</i>

324
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:42,620
<i>various outbreaks are being contained.</i>

325
00:32:44,178 --> 00:32:45,242
<i>Fellow citizens,</i>

326
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:51,540
<i>please refrain from reacting to baseless rumors,</i>

327
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:57,580
<i>and stay in the safety of your homes.</i>

328
00:32:58,134 --> 00:33:01,000
We must stay calm and trust the government,

329
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:04,500
in order to overcome such trying obstacle.

330
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:09,340
<i>We believe that your safety is not in jeopardy.</i>

331
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:24,200
<i>ANALYST KIM</i>

332
00:33:31,140 --> 00:33:32,990
Mommy's phone is off.

333
00:33:37,096 --> 00:33:40,096
<i>Those in front, hurry up!</i>

334
00:33:40,525 --> 00:33:42,025
Soo-an, sit over here.

335
00:33:42,663 --> 00:33:44,963
Don't worry, I'll give her a call.

336
00:33:47,005 --> 00:33:48,605
Jong-Gil, come sit down.

337
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:51,360
You're older, you sit down.

338
00:33:51,380 --> 00:33:52,500
I'm fine, take it.

339
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:54,020
Baby, let's go over there.

340
00:33:58,740 --> 00:34:01,080
Ma'am, take my seat.

341
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:04,220
- I'm okay.
- No, please sit.

342
00:34:08,180 --> 00:34:08,960
Child.

343
00:34:10,030 --> 00:34:10,960
Would you like one?

344
00:34:13,880 --> 00:34:14,760
Thank you.

345
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:17,470
What a great kid.

346
00:34:22,329 --> 00:34:24,730
- We both got seats.
- Keep walking.

347
00:34:25,731 --> 00:34:26,731
<i>That bag...</i>

348
00:34:28,460 --> 00:34:30,720
Soo-an, you didn't have to do that.

349
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:33,860
- Do what?
- Being good.

350
00:34:34,420 --> 00:34:37,120
At a time like this,
only watch out for yourself.

351
00:34:40,413 --> 00:34:41,413
Answer me.

352
00:34:46,620 --> 00:34:49,800
Granny always had knee aches.

353
00:34:51,452 --> 00:34:52,452
Soo-an...

354
00:34:57,840 --> 00:35:00,700
<i>May I have your attention please.</i>

355
00:35:01,300 --> 00:35:04,900
<i>Our train will conclude service at Daejeon station.</i>

356
00:35:05,620 --> 00:35:10,930
<i>Military is deployed there,
and will secure our train.</i>

357
00:35:11,380 --> 00:35:15,000
<i>So once we arrive, please exit the train.</i>

358
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:16,740
<i>I repeat,</i>

359
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:19,920
<i>Daejeon station is our last stop.</i>

360
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:22,400
Which cities can be entered?

361
00:35:22,753 --> 00:35:25,420
Yeosu, Uljin, Busan.
What about Daejeon?

362
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:27,540
Excuse me, I need to use it.

363
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:29,100
What about Daejeon?

364
00:35:29,590 --> 00:35:30,440
<i>Why not?!</i>

365
00:35:32,580 --> 00:35:34,940
Soo-an, stay put.

366
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:39,860
Hey, kiddo.

367
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:41,360
Yes?

368
00:35:41,620 --> 00:35:43,330
Who is he? Your dad?

369
00:35:44,320 --> 00:35:45,040
Yes.

370
00:35:45,290 --> 00:35:46,820
- Real dad?
- Yes.

371
00:35:47,770 --> 00:35:48,980
I wanna know.

372
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:51,500
What does he do?

373
00:35:51,750 --> 00:35:53,750
He's a fund manager.

374
00:35:53,958 --> 00:35:56,157
- Fund manager?
- Yes.

375
00:35:57,043 --> 00:35:58,643
He's a bloodsucker, a bloodsucker

376
00:35:59,700 --> 00:36:01,580
He leaches off others.

377
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:04,460
Don't say that in front of his child.

378
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:05,940
It's okay.

379
00:36:06,740 --> 00:36:09,340
That's what everyone thinks.

380
00:36:15,520 --> 00:36:16,440
Want some?

381
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:19,300
It's what Sleepy eats.

382
00:36:20,876 --> 00:36:23,275
This is Sleepy. Say hello

383
00:36:24,753 --> 00:36:26,954
Baby's name is Sleepy?

384
00:36:27,460 --> 00:36:28,550
No, the fetus name.

385
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:31,120
It's like a nickname,

386
00:36:31,540 --> 00:36:35,380
her dad is too lazy to
come up with a name yet.

387
00:36:37,520 --> 00:36:38,460
Touch her belly.

388
00:36:39,060 --> 00:36:39,890
Right here.

389
00:36:41,540 --> 00:36:42,340
Go on.

390
00:36:48,260 --> 00:36:49,000
Felt it?

391
00:36:50,806 --> 00:36:52,222
I made that.

392
00:36:56,340 --> 00:36:58,500
- You idiot...
- But it's true. No?

393
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:14,820
<i>Mr. Seok, you called me at a bad time.</i>

394
00:37:14,820 --> 00:37:15,720
Wait, wait!

395
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,780
Let me ask you something.

396
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:18,840
<i>What?</i>

397
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:22,180
I'm on KTX to Daejeon.

398
00:37:22,220 --> 00:37:26,150
<i>KTX? Right this minute?</i>

399
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:27,620
Yes, I'm almost there.

400
00:37:28,670 --> 00:37:31,853
Is it true the military is deployed in Daejeon?

401
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,290
<i>Yes, that's correct.</i>

402
00:37:35,634 --> 00:37:38,943
Is that so? It must be safe there.

403
00:37:40,945 --> 00:37:43,206
<i>Well... it's...</i>

404
00:37:44,840 --> 00:37:47,920
Min, it is safe, right?

405
00:37:48,706 --> 00:37:53,802
<i>Once you arrive, you'll be quarantined.</i>

406
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:54,580
What?

407
00:37:58,520 --> 00:38:00,450
I'm with my daughter.

408
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:05,120
Can you help me and my daughter, huh?

409
00:38:07,100 --> 00:38:08,020
<i>But the thing is...</i>

410
00:38:08,020 --> 00:38:11,670
I'll get you a real scoop,
do me a favor.

411
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:17,820
<i>Don't go to the main square,
come to the East one, okay?</i>

412
00:38:17,900 --> 00:38:19,540
<i>I'll let my men know.</i>

413
00:38:20,630 --> 00:38:22,800
Okay, thank you.
Thanks so much.

414
00:38:27,655 --> 00:38:28,655
All dead...

415
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:49,880
What's going on?

416
00:38:50,740 --> 00:38:51,600
So quiet...

417
00:38:51,786 --> 00:38:52,786
Is it Daejeon?

418
00:39:00,304 --> 00:39:01,304
<i>There's nobody.</i>

419
00:39:02,220 --> 00:39:03,440
Why isn't anyone here?

420
00:39:21,380 --> 00:39:22,240
Out of my way.

421
00:40:13,110 --> 00:40:14,911
What's going on back there?

422
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:21,580
This is that violent incident I told you about!

423
00:40:21,620 --> 00:40:22,440
Conductor!

424
00:40:22,680 --> 00:40:24,480
- You're the conductor?
- Yes.

425
00:40:25,300 --> 00:40:26,800
How many can fit in the engine car?

426
00:40:27,100 --> 00:40:29,260
We must uncouple it and go to Busan.

427
00:40:29,300 --> 00:40:30,400
- Uncouple?
- Yes!

428
00:40:30,580 --> 00:40:32,160
- We can't!
- Why not?!

429
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:33,760
It can't be done here.

430
00:40:35,270 --> 00:40:37,120
Then where's the military?

431
00:40:37,791 --> 00:40:38,791
Yeah right.

432
00:40:39,020 --> 00:40:41,240
I only received a report about it...

433
00:40:41,260 --> 00:40:42,860
Where's my business card?

434
00:40:44,580 --> 00:40:46,710
I'm the COO of Stallion Express,

435
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:49,060
all routes into Daejeon are cut off.

436
00:40:49,120 --> 00:40:50,880
Our buses are all rerouted.

437
00:40:51,040 --> 00:40:51,980
But what for?

438
00:40:52,060 --> 00:40:54,440
The city's been quarantined!

439
00:40:54,720 --> 00:40:56,520
They probably won't let us in.

440
00:40:56,800 --> 00:41:01,220
But Busan is still open,
so let's go there!

441
00:41:01,240 --> 00:41:03,620
Wait, if that's true...

442
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:06,110
- we must take others.
- Take who?!

443
00:41:06,140 --> 00:41:08,220
Let's check the station first.

444
00:41:09,020 --> 00:41:09,720
Hey!

445
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:39,240
<i>RESTRICTED AREA</i>

446
00:41:56,980 --> 00:41:58,120
Don't mind them.

447
00:42:04,640 --> 00:42:05,640
<i>Come on Soo-an.</i>

448
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:06,720
Where are we going?

449
00:42:08,020 --> 00:42:09,520
We're going this way.

450
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:12,450
- Just us?
- Yes, let's go.

451
00:42:18,740 --> 00:42:19,580
What is it?

452
00:42:21,350 --> 00:42:23,340
I'm going this way too.

453
00:42:24,117 --> 00:42:27,001
Main square is that way,
just follow the others.

454
00:42:27,100 --> 00:42:28,760
I'm gonna come with you.

455
00:42:29,815 --> 00:42:31,416
I heard your phone call.

456
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:33,910
About pulling you two out.

457
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:38,130
I know others will be quarantined.

458
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:41,800
It's not true, Soo-an.

459
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:43,440
I'll go tell the others.

460
00:42:43,500 --> 00:42:47,270
- Soo-an, you don't have to.
- Of course I do!

461
00:42:47,367 --> 00:42:49,635
Forget them!
We're all on our own!

462
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:55,010
Dad, you only care about yourself.

463
00:42:57,400 --> 00:43:00,950
That's why mommy left.

464
00:43:20,260 --> 00:43:21,360
Soo-an...

465
00:43:23,360 --> 00:43:24,160
Hey!

466
00:43:24,380 --> 00:43:26,240
Here! Over here!

467
00:43:26,420 --> 00:43:27,550
Please help!

468
00:43:29,660 --> 00:43:31,740
Soo-an, stay right here.

469
00:43:52,800 --> 00:43:53,740
Goddamit!

470
00:43:55,720 --> 00:43:56,620
Hold on!

471
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:10,230
Go back up! Go! Go!

472
00:44:28,260 --> 00:44:28,930
Mr. Min...

473
00:44:28,940 --> 00:44:30,640
- <i>Mr. Seok!</i>
- I'm in Daejeon.

474
00:44:30,640 --> 00:44:33,200
<i>Is everything okay there?
I can't contact my men!</i>

475
00:44:33,220 --> 00:44:34,260
What?

476
00:44:34,660 --> 00:44:35,580
<i>Hello?!</i>

477
00:44:35,720 --> 00:44:37,020
Help me...

478
00:45:19,520 --> 00:45:20,950
Come on! Hurry!

479
00:45:33,570 --> 00:45:34,940
Hurry up! Quick!

480
00:45:36,060 --> 00:45:36,820
Take this!

481
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:56,540
Run! Come on!

482
00:46:01,920 --> 00:46:03,200
Asshole! Come on!

483
00:46:11,846 --> 00:46:12,846
Faster!

484
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:16,010
Hold them off!

485
00:46:49,840 --> 00:46:54,080
- Over here! Run!
- This way! Hurry!

486
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:55,620
Here! Here!

487
00:46:59,220 --> 00:47:00,340
This way!

488
00:47:01,512 --> 00:47:02,512
Come on!

489
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:03,840
Hurry!

490
00:47:03,880 --> 00:47:06,200
Why aren't we leaving yet?!

491
00:47:06,680 --> 00:47:08,560
There are still more people!

492
00:47:08,949 --> 00:47:09,949
Hurry up!

493
00:47:10,940 --> 00:47:12,420
Come this way!

494
00:47:13,720 --> 00:47:14,720
Hurry!

495
00:47:14,760 --> 00:47:16,140
Faster! Here!

496
00:47:29,580 --> 00:47:30,610
Granny!

497
00:47:31,451 --> 00:47:32,451
Please get up!

498
00:47:42,940 --> 00:47:44,190
No, stop!

499
00:47:44,820 --> 00:47:45,800
My sister!

500
00:47:54,490 --> 00:47:55,400
Hop on!

501
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:16,220
Me too!

502
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:18,710
Let me in!

503
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:20,480
Please!

504
00:48:38,640 --> 00:48:41,200
How much longer?
We have to leave!

505
00:48:41,220 --> 00:48:43,210
No! my friends aren't here yet!

506
00:48:44,460 --> 00:48:46,380
Those onboard must survive!

507
00:48:47,020 --> 00:48:47,740
Am I right?

508
00:48:54,860 --> 00:48:55,700
Conductor.

509
00:48:56,900 --> 00:48:59,240
Please... depart.

510
00:49:20,020 --> 00:49:21,480
Run! Let's go!

511
00:49:37,420 --> 00:49:38,660
Look, the train!

512
00:49:38,940 --> 00:49:39,800
Run faster!

513
00:49:59,295 --> 00:50:00,762
Snap out of it, idiot!

514
00:50:30,220 --> 00:50:31,100
Watch out!

515
00:50:52,570 --> 00:50:57,260
Control, 101 could not dock
at Daejeon due to the outbreak.

516
00:50:57,520 --> 00:51:00,440
Advise which station is available to dock, over.

517
00:51:00,867 --> 00:51:05,697
<i>101, due to unstable comm,
it is difficult to advise.</i>

518
00:51:06,120 --> 00:51:11,080
Control, is 101 clear to reach Busan? Over.

519
00:51:13,902 --> 00:51:17,175
<i>101, we'll clear your route to Busan.</i>

520
00:51:17,240 --> 00:51:18,150
<i>Control center, out.</i>

521
00:51:19,680 --> 00:51:22,260
Advise when you make contact with Busan.

522
00:51:23,360 --> 00:51:24,280
101, out.

523
00:52:40,220 --> 00:52:42,600
<i>Attention everyone.</i>

524
00:52:43,061 --> 00:52:48,137
<i>For those safety of those on board,
we'll head straight for Busan.</i>

525
00:52:48,480 --> 00:52:50,180
We won't be making any stops.

526
00:52:51,840 --> 00:52:53,960
Conductor, can you hear me?

527
00:52:54,520 --> 00:52:55,660
<i>Go ahead.</i>

528
00:52:56,240 --> 00:52:57,840
Were you able to contact Busan?

529
00:52:58,180 --> 00:53:01,010
<i>No, the communication is erratic.</i>

530
00:53:02,580 --> 00:53:04,500
Full speed, no matter what!

531
00:53:04,900 --> 00:53:06,860
Or we won't get in, understand?!

532
00:53:14,820 --> 00:53:16,480
Young-Gook, where are you?!

533
00:53:19,140 --> 00:53:22,060
I thought you were dead!

534
00:53:22,520 --> 00:53:23,560
I'm sorry!

535
00:53:26,010 --> 00:53:27,760
No one else made it!

536
00:53:29,120 --> 00:53:30,180
I'm sorry.

537
00:53:41,690 --> 00:53:43,720
- Baby?
- <i>Mister!</i>

538
00:53:44,844 --> 00:53:47,577
Why are you answering?
Where are you?

539
00:53:47,570 --> 00:53:49,820
We're, we're in the train washroom!

540
00:53:49,860 --> 00:53:52,630
Washroom? Which car?

541
00:53:52,870 --> 00:53:55,520
Well... it's...

542
00:53:55,560 --> 00:53:56,860
Car 13!

543
00:53:56,940 --> 00:53:58,740
- Get your ass over here!
- Baby!

544
00:54:02,620 --> 00:54:03,780
Was that my kid?

545
00:54:03,900 --> 00:54:04,840
Is she okay?

546
00:54:05,340 --> 00:54:06,940
Washroom in car 13.

547
00:54:22,140 --> 00:54:23,120
Gonna pass through?

548
00:54:25,510 --> 00:54:27,740
Let's say you got through and rescue them,

549
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:29,380
how will you come back?

550
00:54:34,080 --> 00:54:35,350
In car 15,

551
00:54:37,020 --> 00:54:38,600
people are gathered there.

552
00:54:44,680 --> 00:54:46,580
<i>CAR 9</i>

553
00:55:03,820 --> 00:55:05,640
Only 4 cars away.

554
00:55:07,739 --> 00:55:08,739
I'll lead.

555
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:11,480
You in the middle,

556
00:55:13,120 --> 00:55:14,120
and you in the back.

557
00:55:17,620 --> 00:55:19,580
Block anyone attacking from the rear.

558
00:55:31,840 --> 00:55:33,880
I heard you're a fund manager.

559
00:55:36,960 --> 00:55:38,460
Then you're an expert,

560
00:55:39,680 --> 00:55:41,620
at leaving useless people behind.

561
00:55:48,740 --> 00:55:50,380
Wait till we exit the tunnel.

562
00:56:05,400 --> 00:56:06,510
Let's go.

563
00:57:17,820 --> 00:57:18,520
Come on!

564
00:57:21,520 --> 00:57:22,400
Let's go!

565
00:57:39,140 --> 00:57:39,960
Move.

566
00:59:23,880 --> 00:59:24,980
Out of the way.

567
00:59:28,920 --> 00:59:32,500
They stopped once we entered the tunnel, right?

568
00:59:33,560 --> 00:59:35,080
Probably because of the darkness.

569
00:59:35,120 --> 00:59:37,060
Yeah, I think so too.

570
00:59:40,000 --> 00:59:41,820
There are even more here.

571
00:59:42,960 --> 00:59:44,250
What do we do now?

572
00:59:45,640 --> 00:59:47,000
There's no way around it.

573
00:59:47,880 --> 00:59:48,800
Let's go.

574
00:59:52,900 --> 00:59:55,000
Hey, can I borrow your cell?

575
01:01:59,760 --> 01:02:01,180
Get that out of my face.

576
01:02:03,480 --> 01:02:04,640
Yo, douche.

577
01:02:05,940 --> 01:02:09,960
Felt good to see
your kid thanks to me, huh?

578
01:02:10,020 --> 01:02:12,040
Are you grateful or what?

579
01:02:12,680 --> 01:02:14,800
Why is your ringtone so tacky?

580
01:02:16,000 --> 01:02:17,700
What's wrong with it?

581
01:02:19,620 --> 01:02:21,780
How do I change it?

582
01:02:23,422 --> 01:02:27,398
Am I funny?
You little rat.

583
01:02:28,220 --> 01:02:29,360
How tall are you?

584
01:02:29,560 --> 01:02:30,760
181cm.

585
01:02:31,740 --> 01:02:34,700
10km away, at 300km/h...

586
01:02:34,760 --> 01:02:35,580
What?

587
01:02:38,900 --> 01:02:42,040
2 minutes... upcoming tunnel
will give us 2 minutes.

588
01:02:42,160 --> 01:02:44,230
- Can we do it?
- We gotta, we gotta...

589
01:02:45,530 --> 01:02:50,660
If we miss this one,
there's another in 3km...

590
01:02:51,580 --> 01:02:54,020
I bet you never get to
play with your daughter.

591
01:02:55,980 --> 01:02:57,600
When she gets older,

592
01:02:59,140 --> 01:03:02,090
she'll understand why you work so hard.

593
01:03:04,220 --> 01:03:07,430
Dads get all the bad rap and no praise,

594
01:03:08,230 --> 01:03:10,540
but it's all about sacrifice, right?

595
01:03:14,070 --> 01:03:17,200
What's with the look?
Did I sound cool?

596
01:03:25,820 --> 01:03:27,440
<i>People rescued.
Heading over now.</i>

597
01:03:28,951 --> 01:03:30,550
My friend's coming here!

598
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:33,180
What did you say?

599
01:03:33,210 --> 01:03:36,060
My friend from another car is coming over.

600
01:03:36,590 --> 01:03:38,580
- Who's coming?
- My friend!

601
01:03:38,880 --> 01:03:42,380
He was in car 9,
and he rescued some people.

602
01:03:42,820 --> 01:03:43,660
Rescued?

603
01:03:45,560 --> 01:03:50,090
From there to here,
passing through those monsters?

604
01:03:51,280 --> 01:03:52,480
Without any injuries?

605
01:03:54,160 --> 01:03:55,700
You sure they're not infected?

606
01:03:57,070 --> 01:03:59,680
Are you damn sure?!

607
01:04:01,300 --> 01:04:03,000
What do you mean?

608
01:04:03,140 --> 01:04:05,770
Look, look at them.

609
01:04:06,480 --> 01:04:07,880
At a moment like this,

610
01:04:08,280 --> 01:04:12,830
no one knows what
happened to their families.

611
01:04:13,560 --> 01:04:18,370
We don't even know if
your damn friends are infected!

612
01:04:18,780 --> 01:04:21,490
But allow them in here?! Huh?!

613
01:04:25,940 --> 01:04:27,680
I don't believe this.

614
01:04:37,400 --> 01:04:38,380
Sir,

615
01:04:40,940 --> 01:04:43,100
please say something.

616
01:04:44,160 --> 01:04:45,720
They'll be here soon.

617
01:04:47,880 --> 01:04:49,360
Sir!

618
01:08:37,600 --> 01:08:38,720
Get over here.

619
01:08:47,940 --> 01:08:48,720
One!

620
01:08:51,340 --> 01:08:52,160
Two!

621
01:08:58,960 --> 01:08:59,760
Run!

622
01:09:13,380 --> 01:09:14,460
Jin-Hee! Jin-Hee!

623
01:09:17,930 --> 01:09:19,300
Hurry the hell up!

624
01:09:29,400 --> 01:09:30,300
Open up!

625
01:09:31,240 --> 01:09:33,860
Hey! Open this door!

626
01:09:35,620 --> 01:09:36,240
Jin-hee!

627
01:09:36,600 --> 01:09:37,380
Open this door!

628
01:09:53,780 --> 01:09:56,950
- Open up!
- Jin-Hee! Jin-Hee!

629
01:10:07,540 --> 01:10:08,970
Open it now!

630
01:10:10,040 --> 01:10:11,100
It won't budge!

631
01:10:11,370 --> 01:10:12,520
I can't open it!

632
01:10:12,649 --> 01:10:13,649
Smash it!

633
01:10:14,620 --> 01:10:15,480
Stand back!

634
01:10:22,350 --> 01:10:23,480
Hurry up!

635
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:29,360
Dammit!

636
01:10:53,860 --> 01:10:55,220
You stupid idiots!

637
01:11:09,060 --> 01:11:09,890
Come on!

638
01:11:21,600 --> 01:11:22,540
In-Gil!

639
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:29,100
Young-Gook!

640
01:11:32,700 --> 01:11:33,900
Stand back!

641
01:11:33,920 --> 01:11:34,800
Young-Gook!

642
01:12:09,660 --> 01:12:10,740
Stay away!

643
01:12:17,920 --> 01:12:21,680
Stay back, baby.
Please go!

644
01:12:28,260 --> 01:12:29,640
Buddy, hey!

645
01:12:31,980 --> 01:12:33,160
Take her and leave.

646
01:12:34,360 --> 01:12:35,820
You have to go!

647
01:12:37,380 --> 01:12:38,920
I said go, douche!

648
01:12:40,800 --> 01:12:42,840
I'm getting tired, please go.

649
01:12:46,580 --> 01:12:49,640
- Please take...
- ...care of her. I will.

650
01:12:51,200 --> 01:12:54,880
I'll hold them off, just go!

651
01:13:05,300 --> 01:13:07,120
I'm... I'm sorry.

652
01:13:17,993 --> 01:13:19,993
We have to go, let's go!

653
01:13:22,010 --> 01:13:23,080
Yoon Su-yun!

654
01:13:25,600 --> 01:13:27,420
Our baby's name!

655
01:13:28,680 --> 01:13:29,720
Got it?

656
01:15:29,939 --> 01:15:31,207
Why did you do it?!

657
01:15:33,810 --> 01:15:34,980
You bastard!

658
01:15:36,948 --> 01:15:38,416
We could've save them!

659
01:15:41,110 --> 01:15:41,960
Why?!

660
01:15:43,420 --> 01:15:44,980
He's infected!

661
01:15:46,540 --> 01:15:48,280
He's one of them!

662
01:15:48,860 --> 01:15:50,090
This guy's infected!

663
01:15:50,600 --> 01:15:52,520
His eyes! Look at his eyes!

664
01:15:52,700 --> 01:15:54,940
He'll become one of them!

665
01:15:55,360 --> 01:15:56,790
Do you all want to die?!

666
01:15:57,100 --> 01:15:58,520
We must throw them out!

667
01:16:09,480 --> 01:16:12,270
Those of you who just arrived,

668
01:16:13,292 --> 01:16:15,625
I don't think you can stay with us.

669
01:16:17,540 --> 01:16:19,480
Please move to the vestibule.

670
01:16:34,680 --> 01:16:35,580
Just go!

671
01:16:40,780 --> 01:16:41,700
Get out!

672
01:16:48,380 --> 01:16:49,720
Get out now!

673
01:16:51,720 --> 01:16:52,540
Hurry up!

674
01:16:53,720 --> 01:16:54,640
Move!

675
01:16:57,220 --> 01:16:58,480
Go!

676
01:16:59,200 --> 01:17:00,420
Leave us!

677
01:17:00,800 --> 01:17:02,000
Get the hell out!

678
01:17:04,698 --> 01:17:05,698
Out now!

679
01:17:07,640 --> 01:17:08,680
Hurry!

680
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:15,200
It'll be safer for you to stay here.

681
01:17:15,200 --> 01:17:18,210
No, I don't want to stay.

682
01:17:19,810 --> 01:17:20,961
I'm coming with you.

683
01:17:20,980 --> 01:17:21,700
But...

684
01:17:22,220 --> 01:17:23,530
Get the hell out!

685
01:17:24,120 --> 01:17:25,920
What are you waiting for!

686
01:17:26,540 --> 01:17:27,900
Okay, let's go.

687
01:17:30,620 --> 01:17:33,000
Get out! Rest of you!

688
01:17:33,676 --> 01:17:34,676
Get out!

689
01:17:35,140 --> 01:17:37,020
Get out of here!

690
01:17:55,060 --> 01:17:55,940
Let's go.

691
01:18:33,480 --> 01:18:34,910
Tie it faster!

692
01:18:36,000 --> 01:18:37,100
More ties! Neckties!

693
01:18:38,420 --> 01:18:40,020
Shut up! I'm working on it!

694
01:18:55,540 --> 01:18:56,680
Yun In-Gil

695
01:18:57,640 --> 01:18:58,870
Great name.

696
01:19:00,240 --> 01:19:04,320
Always helping others
instead of yourself.

697
01:19:08,600 --> 01:19:10,520
Why did you live like that?

698
01:19:12,200 --> 01:19:14,480
What was the point?

699
01:19:15,850 --> 01:19:17,180
So stupid...

700
01:19:24,420 --> 01:19:25,910
Shut up! Be quiet!

701
01:19:27,140 --> 01:19:28,460
Stay in your seat!

702
01:19:29,480 --> 01:19:31,940
What a load of shit.

703
01:19:36,770 --> 01:19:39,000
Finish up and do the other side too.

704
01:19:49,980 --> 01:19:53,880
Thank you for everyting.

705
01:19:55,600 --> 01:19:56,520
That woman...

706
01:19:56,560 --> 01:19:57,960
Stop her!

707
01:20:52,060 --> 01:20:54,700
Control, this is Busan-bound 101!

708
01:20:54,800 --> 01:20:56,740
Requesting current situation in Busan, over.

709
01:20:58,440 --> 01:20:59,370
Control?!

710
01:21:00,120 --> 01:21:00,980
Control!

711
01:22:27,800 --> 01:22:29,460
It's your birthday...

712
01:22:34,157 --> 01:22:35,157
Don't worry.

713
01:22:36,040 --> 01:22:37,920
I'll take you to mom no matter what.

714
01:22:42,300 --> 01:22:44,000
Aren't you scared?

715
01:22:49,940 --> 01:22:50,860
Of course I am.

716
01:22:53,200 --> 01:22:54,150
I'm scared too.

717
01:22:59,310 --> 01:23:01,160
I was so scared.

718
01:23:01,980 --> 01:23:04,840
I thought I'd never see you again.

719
01:23:07,200 --> 01:23:12,020
I practiced that song just for you.

720
01:23:16,360 --> 01:23:18,340
That's why I couldn't sing.

721
01:23:20,880 --> 01:23:22,560
Because I didn't see you.

722
01:23:30,120 --> 01:23:32,360
Will you stay with me?

723
01:23:47,580 --> 01:23:49,520
<i>EX-WIFE</i>

724
01:24:00,540 --> 01:24:05,000
<i>The person you're calling is not available.</i>

725
01:24:15,280 --> 01:24:18,740
<i>ANALYST KIM</i>

726
01:24:21,520 --> 01:24:22,600
Yes, Kim.

727
01:24:24,440 --> 01:24:26,300
<i>Have you arrived in Busan?</i>

728
01:24:26,345 --> 01:24:29,078
Not yet, where are you?
Is it okay there?

729
01:24:30,820 --> 01:24:33,100
<i>Busan succeeded in initial defense.</i>

730
01:24:33,640 --> 01:24:36,480
What?
Are you sure?

731
01:24:36,800 --> 01:24:38,260
Where did you hear that news, huh?

732
01:24:39,300 --> 01:24:40,160
<i>Boss...</i>

733
01:24:41,180 --> 01:24:43,500
<i>all of this started at YT BioTech.</i>

734
01:24:46,000 --> 01:24:50,020
<i>It's our project!
Our plant started all of this!</i>

735
01:24:54,420 --> 01:24:55,460
<i>Boss...</i>

736
01:24:56,340 --> 01:24:59,080
<i>please tell me it's not our fault, eh?</i>

737
01:25:00,500 --> 01:25:03,800
<i>We're only doing our jobs, right?</i>

738
01:25:04,840 --> 01:25:06,980
<i>Is this my fault, huh?</i>

739
01:25:10,500 --> 01:25:11,800
It's...

740
01:25:12,760 --> 01:25:14,120
It's not your fault.

741
01:25:18,192 --> 01:25:19,192
<i>Thank you...</i>

742
01:25:21,420 --> 01:25:22,280
Kim...

743
01:27:07,580 --> 01:27:09,320
Attention please.

744
01:27:09,740 --> 01:27:13,470
<i>Due to a blockage on our track,</i>

745
01:27:13,960 --> 01:27:16,200
<i>we have stopped at East Daegu Station.</i>

746
01:27:16,460 --> 01:27:20,180
<i>We should either wait for the rescue team,</i>

747
01:27:20,240 --> 01:27:25,060
<i>or we'll have to reach Busan in another train.</i>

748
01:27:25,680 --> 01:27:27,700
<i>As soon as I end this announcement,</i>

749
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:33,680
<i>I will find a working train
and put it on the left most track.</i>

750
01:27:33,740 --> 01:27:34,380
What's going on?

751
01:27:34,400 --> 01:27:37,100
<i>I repeat, left most track.</i>

752
01:27:37,470 --> 01:27:41,987
If you're alive,
please transfer safely.

753
01:27:44,140 --> 01:27:45,200
Godspeed.

754
01:28:51,220 --> 01:28:52,880
Will there be a rescue?

755
01:28:55,740 --> 01:28:57,700
I heard that Busan is safe.

756
01:29:00,300 --> 01:29:01,620
We have to move now.

757
01:30:47,140 --> 01:30:47,960
Coast clear?

758
01:30:51,200 --> 01:30:51,950
Yeah.

759
01:30:55,269 --> 01:30:56,269
You go ahead.

760
01:31:20,860 --> 01:31:22,540
We've have to find a way across.

761
01:31:46,490 --> 01:31:47,600
What in the...

762
01:32:00,280 --> 01:32:01,200
Over here!

763
01:32:38,560 --> 01:32:39,440
No...

764
01:32:39,700 --> 01:32:40,560
Oh no...

765
01:32:42,980 --> 01:32:44,380
What now!

766
01:32:45,220 --> 01:32:47,310
We have to move, come on!

767
01:32:55,560 --> 01:32:57,060
Jin-Hee, let's go!

768
01:33:13,540 --> 01:33:14,360
Stand back!

769
01:33:27,671 --> 01:33:28,671
Jin-Hee!

770
01:33:43,180 --> 01:33:43,940
Jin-Hee!

771
01:33:56,000 --> 01:33:57,140
This can't be...

772
01:34:03,380 --> 01:34:04,420
I'm sorry...

773
01:34:27,560 --> 01:34:37,900
<i>Daddy! Wake up!</i>

774
01:34:38,160 --> 01:34:42,470
Daddy! Daddy!

775
01:34:57,820 --> 01:34:59,330
What's going on?

776
01:35:03,480 --> 01:35:05,440
Come on faster! Faster!

777
01:35:06,460 --> 01:35:07,440
Faster!

778
01:35:13,020 --> 01:35:14,310
Dammit!

779
01:35:31,211 --> 01:35:32,211
Help!

780
01:36:15,280 --> 01:36:16,860
Soo-an, come here!

781
01:36:21,620 --> 01:36:23,060
Soo-an, Soo-an!

782
01:36:39,720 --> 01:36:40,980
Mister!

783
01:36:59,460 --> 01:37:00,320
Soo-an!

784
01:37:00,440 --> 01:37:02,180
Soo-an, come here!

785
01:37:02,920 --> 01:37:03,860
Mister...

786
01:37:03,880 --> 01:37:05,620
Go! Hurry!

787
01:37:06,670 --> 01:37:07,440
Come on!

788
01:37:07,800 --> 01:37:08,600
Hurry!

789
01:37:28,360 --> 01:37:29,280
Let's go!

790
01:38:55,540 --> 01:38:56,940
Hurry! Hurry!

791
01:39:00,540 --> 01:39:01,540
Daddy!

792
01:41:23,280 --> 01:41:24,300
Mister.

793
01:41:26,200 --> 01:41:27,580
Please bring me to Busan.

794
01:41:30,700 --> 01:41:34,700
Please help me.
Please... please...

795
01:41:35,700 --> 01:41:37,800
My mother is waiting for me.

796
01:41:41,560 --> 01:41:47,890
Please bring me home.
<i>giving his address</i>

797
01:41:51,160 --> 01:41:52,940
Please save me.

798
01:41:56,800 --> 01:41:57,520
You're...

799
01:41:59,220 --> 01:42:00,340
...already infected.

800
01:42:06,600 --> 01:42:07,460
No.

801
01:42:09,420 --> 01:42:10,280
No.

802
01:42:11,340 --> 01:42:12,240
No.

803
01:42:13,440 --> 01:42:18,600
No, no,
no... no...

804
01:44:43,980 --> 01:44:44,980
Soo-an come here

805
01:44:45,680 --> 01:44:47,320
Sit here.

806
01:44:50,540 --> 01:44:52,060
Listen to me...

807
01:44:53,200 --> 01:44:57,060
Here is the throttle,
the brakes.

808
01:44:58,240 --> 01:45:00,260
When you need to stop,
pull the brakes.

809
01:45:06,480 --> 01:45:07,240
Soo-an...

810
01:45:09,480 --> 01:45:11,500
Look at me...
look at me, Soo-an.

811
01:45:16,600 --> 01:45:18,060
Look at me, look at me...

812
01:45:19,340 --> 01:45:20,100
Soo-an...

813
01:45:21,000 --> 01:45:21,860
listen to me.

814
01:45:23,320 --> 01:45:27,060
You must stay with her, okay?

815
01:45:28,220 --> 01:45:30,040
Busan is still safe.

816
01:45:30,340 --> 01:45:33,980
- That is why... that is why...
- Don't go!

817
01:45:35,100 --> 01:45:37,400
Don't go, father!
Come with us.

818
01:45:39,000 --> 01:45:40,060
Please don't leave me...

819
01:45:40,860 --> 01:45:42,340
Don't go...

820
01:45:43,900 --> 01:45:45,360
come with us.

821
01:45:47,580 --> 01:45:48,840
